      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The discrepancy you're experiencing is a common issue in inventory management, and it's essential to address it promptly. The standard industry methods for auditing shrinkage typically involve a combination of manual and automated processes. You can start by conducting a physical count of the inventory on the floor, using a process called a \"count and reconcile\" to verify the discrepancies. This might involve re-counting the inventory items, checking for any discrepancies between the system and the physical count, and reconciling the differences. It's a good idea to involve a team of auditors to ensure accuracy and fairness.",
